00:01:08.420 --> 00:01:10.760
He's also the co-founder
of the Gottman Institute

00:01:10.760 --> 00:01:13.330
with his wife, and
he's professor emeritus

00:01:13.330 --> 00:01:15.790
of psychology at the
University of Washington,

00:01:15.790 --> 00:01:19.500
where he founded the love
lab to research couples.

00:01:19.500 --> 00:01:21.640
Now, Doctor Julie
Schwartz Gotttman

00:01:21.640 --> 00:01:25.200
is the co-founder and president
of the Gotttman Institute.

00:01:25.200 --> 00:01:29.425
She's also highly recognized
as a clinical psychologist, who

00:01:29.425 --> 00:01:32.370
has worked with distressed
couples, abuse and trauma

00:01:32.370 --> 00:01:35.140
survivors, substance
abusers and their partners,

00:01:35.140 --> 00:01:37.820
and cancer patients
and their families.

00:01:37.820 --> 00:01:40.860
She's also the co-author of
the immensely popular "The Art

00:01:40.860 --> 00:01:43.970
and Science of Love" weekend
workshops for couples,

00:01:43.970 --> 00:01:46.230
and the author of
four books including

00:01:46.230 --> 00:01:48.440
"Ten Lesson to
Transform your Marriage"

00:01:48.440 --> 00:01:50.270
and "Baby Makes Three."

00:01:50.270 --> 00:01:51.880
Wow, those are
quite introductions.

00:01:51.880 --> 00:01:52.380
[LAUGHTER]

00:01:52.380 --> 00:01:53.180
JULIE GOTTMAN: Yeah

00:01:53.180 --> 00:01:56.646
LOGAN URY: So, thank you
so much for joining us,

00:01:56.646 --> 00:02:03.560
and [APPLAUSE] So,
for those people

00:02:03.560 --> 00:02:05.890
in the audience who aren't
as familiar with your work,

00:02:05.890 --> 00:02:07.890
I want to start
at the beginning.

00:02:07.890 --> 00:02:10.840
Who are the four horsemen,
and why is their presence

