00:47:51.040 --> 00:47:53.590
to look out for, in terms
of that community support--

00:47:53.590 --> 00:47:56.700
is because the marriage
has been arranged,

00:47:56.700 --> 00:48:00.650
the people who arranged it
have great investment in it

00:48:00.650 --> 00:48:02.920
continuing.

00:48:02.920 --> 00:48:07.110
And in the event that there is
some domestic violence, which

00:48:07.110 --> 00:48:11.020
I've seen a lot of, they do
not want to support, typically,

00:48:11.020 --> 00:48:14.106
the wife to leave.

00:48:14.106 --> 00:48:16.840
And they want her
to stay, and they

00:48:16.840 --> 00:48:19.850
tell her to put up with it, it's
been put up for generations,

00:48:19.850 --> 00:48:20.650
oh well.

00:48:20.650 --> 00:48:22.904
It's OK, be a good wife.

00:48:22.904 --> 00:48:25.548
And that is a problem.

00:48:25.548 --> 00:48:26.298
JOHN GOTTMAN: Yep.

00:48:26.298 --> 00:48:27.423
JULIE GOTTMAN: Big problem.

00:48:33.310 --> 00:48:41.589
AUDIENCE: Hi so-- [LAUGHTER]
so I read several of your books

00:48:41.589 --> 00:48:42.672
and I really enjoyed them.

00:48:42.672 --> 00:48:44.130
But I notice a lot
of your research

00:48:44.130 --> 00:48:45.840
is focused on long term couples.

00:48:45.840 --> 00:48:49.590
For people who are single,
or just starting to date,

00:48:49.590 --> 00:48:55.330
do you have any books that you
recommend or that you wrote?

00:48:55.330 --> 00:48:57.270
JULIE GOTTMAN: So,
part of the problem

00:48:57.270 --> 00:49:01.160
is that there has been
this much research

00:49:01.160 --> 00:49:04.685
on dating and single
people, and how

00:49:04.685 --> 00:49:07.370
to make a good relationship.

00:49:07.370 --> 00:49:09.550
So all of the
internet stuff, I mean

00:49:09.550 --> 00:49:14.260
there is no research
that backs it up.

00:49:14.260 --> 00:49:17.350
And so we need to
do that research,

00:49:17.350 --> 00:49:18.970
we would love to
do that research,

00:49:18.970 --> 00:49:21.000
we have talked about
