00:49:23.440 --> 00:49:29.540
But, it's a very valid thing to
be looking at because people,

00:49:29.540 --> 00:49:31.840
especially if they're coming
out of divorced homes,

00:49:31.840 --> 00:49:36.440
and many are, don't know
what to look for in terms

00:49:36.440 --> 00:49:38.430
of a decent relationship.

00:49:38.430 --> 00:49:40.920
So, good question.

00:49:40.920 --> 00:49:42.920
JOHN GOTTMAN: You know,
one of the things that's

00:49:42.920 --> 00:49:47.590
so interesting about research on
relationships at the beginning,

00:49:47.590 --> 00:49:51.100
selecting somebody, is that
the research is just awful.

00:49:51.100 --> 00:49:57.280
And part of the problem is
that these matching services

00:49:57.280 --> 00:49:59.570
are using the wrong algorithm.

00:49:59.570 --> 00:50:02.670
They're trying to help
people find their clone,

00:50:02.670 --> 00:50:05.120
and find somebody
just like you, has

00:50:05.120 --> 00:50:07.420
the same interest,
the same philosophy

00:50:07.420 --> 00:50:10.150
of life, the same personality.

00:50:10.150 --> 00:50:14.900
And for what we know
about, how pheromones

00:50:14.900 --> 00:50:17.880
work in initial
selection-- people

00:50:17.880 --> 00:50:20.710
select t-shirts that's
smell good, based

00:50:20.710 --> 00:50:22.770
upon the pheromones there.

00:50:22.770 --> 00:50:27.950
They're selecting their
genetically more diverse

00:50:27.950 --> 00:50:28.770
person.

00:50:28.770 --> 00:50:31.080
On the major
histocompatibility complex

00:50:31.080 --> 00:50:34.420
they're selecting people
who are different from them,

00:50:34.420 --> 00:50:35.700
very different.

00:50:35.700 --> 00:50:38.940
So, we've got the
wrong algorithm there,

00:50:38.940 --> 00:50:43.410
and that's just an
indicator that we really

00:50:43.410 --> 00:50:46.600
don't know how to help
select the right mate.

00:50:46.600 --> 00:50:52.230
But I think that the guide is to
find somebody who really likes

00:50:52.230 --> 00:50:54.780
the way you laugh,
thinks you're funny,

00:50:54.780 --> 00:50:58.100
and really enjoys your company
and you enjoy their company

00:50:58.100 --> 00:51:02.521
and that's really the best
guide we have at the moment.

00:51:02.521 --> 00:51:04.520
LOGAN URY: I'd love to
